OB:
In the provided bug report, it is mentioned that BidiUtil in the Win32 version includes the following line of code:
static Callback callback = new Callback (BidiUtil.class, 'windowProc', 4);
The 'BidiUtil.class' part is equivalent to 'Class.forName('org...BidiUtil')', which is the source of the problem. This code results in a method throwing a NoClassDefFoundError, which is not defined in the CLDC class libraries. This poses an issue for the CLDC version of SWT. However, this issue might only become apparent when using verification tools like jxeLink, as the compiler generates the call automatically without raising errors.

EB:
The expected behavior is to eliminate the problem described above. To achieve this, it is suggested that the line of code be modified as follows:
static Callback callback = new Callback (new BidiUtil().getClass(), 'windowProc', 4);
While this change hasn't been tested, it is believed to produce the same result while resolving the issue caused by the original code.
